<node TEXT="organicgardening.com &gt; Learn-and-grow &gt; The-secret-to-huge-potato-harvests" ID="ID_940270505" CREATED="1423672892250" MODIFIED="1423672892250" LINK="http://www.organicgardening.com/learn-and-grow/the-secret-to-huge-potato-harvests"/>
<node TEXT="Sweet" ID="ID_964544955" CREATED="1424084611810" MODIFIED="1429466623256">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="17" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="In the right conditions, sweet potatoes are tremendously easy to grow. They take up a fair amount of space as they vine across the ground and they need a lengthy growing season, but if you can get them in the ground early enough, even many cold region gardeners can have success with sweet potatoes. You&#x2019;ll need a minimum of 90 days from first frost to last. And just like regular potatoes, sweet potatoes store well for winter use. Sweet potatoes provide about 115 calories for a one-cup serving." ID="ID_47231352" CREATED="1424084653747" MODIFIED="1424084655728"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Russet" ID="ID_1832047161" CREATED="1424084620699" MODIFIED="1429466623260">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="17" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="These tubers are easy to grow. Once the plants are well established, you can carefully dig in and harvest tiny &#x201c;new potatoes&#x201d; for summertime meals. When the leaves start to die off later in the season, you&#x2019;ll dig up the entire plant to harvest the full-sized potatoes. Be sure to include some Russet potatoes in your plan; these will keep through the winter. A regular &#x2018;ol potato has about 160 calories." ID="ID_46612713" CREATED="1424084582291" MODIFIED="1424084584947"/>
</node>
